This course will focus on the role that culture plays in business and management and the impacts of cultural differences on business and management practices. This includes language, habits, traditions, nationality, religion, gender and age. Students will learn how to manage different staff within an organisation, including their education and training needs, as well as managing consumer and client relationships. Emphasis will also be placed on the challenges of doing global business in national, regional and local contexts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to analyse the role of culture in business and management, to assess the impact of cultural differences on business and management practices, and to evaluate how cultural differences can be managed in business and management situations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the students will gain an understanding of: * the role of culture in business and management; * the impact of cultural differences on business and management practices; * the management of cultural dilemmas and conflicts; * the educational and training needs of managers and staff for dealing with different cultural groups; * the different cultural needs of customers and clients.
